Run bench CLI commands in the current project context.

Examples:
  weg bench migrate           # Run migrations
  weg bench console           # Open Python console
  weg bench list-apps         # List installed apps
  weg bench frappe --help     # Show all frappe commands

Usage:
  weg bench [flags]
  weg bench [command]

Available Commands:
  current     Show current bench
  drop        Remove a bench
  list        List all weg-managed benches
  new         Create a new traditional bench

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for bench

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg bench [command] --help" for more information about a command.
